Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Put the @cornflour{20%g} into a large #bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix to combine.

Cut the @British chicken breasts{2} lengthways into 1cm wide strips.

Add the chicken strips to the bowl and turn them over in the cornflour to coat well.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Put a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough oil to completely coat the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan, reduce the heat to medium-high and fry until golden-brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes} total.

Turn every ~{2-3%minutes} and adjust the heat as necessary. Discard any cornflour left in the bowl.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat and place the chicken onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks.

In a small bowl, add the tomato chunks, @red wine vinegar{12%ml} and the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together.

When everything's nearly ready, pop the @plain taco tortillas{3.96} onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

In a small bowl, add the @mayonnaise{64%g} and @chipotle paste{20%g} and stir to combine.

> Add less chipotle if you'd prefer things milder.

To assemble your wraps, lay the warmed tortillas on your plates (2 per person).

Spread a spoonful of chipotle mayo over each, then top with fried chicken strips, tomato salad and a sprinkle of grated cheese.

Roll up the wraps and serve the chips alongside.

Enjoy!